 P(4-K^2 \leq x) = P(\sqrt{4-x} \leq K \leq \infty) + P(-\infty \leq K \leq -\sqrt{4-x}) 
 P(\sqrt{4-x} \leq K \leq \infty) + P(-\infty \leq K \leq -\sqrt{4-x}) = 2P(\sqrt{4-x} \leq K \leq \infty) 
 2\int^{1}_{\sqrt{4-x}}f(t) dt \\ =\frac{3}{2}\int^{1}_{\sqrt{4-x}}1-t^2 dt \\ =\frac{3}{2}\left.\left(t-\frac{t^3}{3}\right)\right|_{\sqrt{4-x}}^1 \\ =\frac{3}{2}\left(\left(1-\frac{1}{3}\right)-\left(\sqrt{4-x}-\frac{(4-x)^{3/2}}{3}\right)\right) \\ =1-\frac{1}{2}\left(x-1\right)\sqrt{4-x} \\ 
